Title: Contract Renewal under Uncertainty.
Author-Name: Andersen, T-M ; Christensen, M-S
Keywords: UNCERTAINTY ; ECONOMETRICS ; PRICES ; INFLATION
Length: 39 pages
Abstract: The incentive to call for contract renewal to adjust prices is considered from a bilateral perspective in a setting changes in outside opportunities drive the incentive to renew contracts and costs preclude continuous renewal. A model encompassing several contract forms is formulated, and the existence of an equilibrium to the bilateral renewal game is established.
